The Navigators</a></div>\n  <p>Since 1933, The Navigators has been introducing Jesus to those who don't know Him and helping those who do know Jesus deepen their relationship with Him. We train others to continue this discipleship process where they live, work, and play. Today, Navigators serve in more than 100 countries.</p>\n  <div class=\"read-more\"><a href=\"/About-Us\">Learn More</a></div>\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"feature fourcol\">\n  <figure><a href=\"http://www.navpress.com/\" target=\"_blank\"><span><img title=\"What We Do\" alttext=\"What We Do Alt Text\" src=\"www_navigators_org/media/Photos/Home%20Page/cta-img-3.jpg?width=900&amp;amp;height=422&amp;amp;ext=.jpg\"></span></a></figure>\n  <div class=\"title\"><a href=\"http://www.navpress.com/\" target=\"_blank\">NavPress</a></div>\n  <p>NavPress advances the calling of The Navigators by bringing biblically rooted, culturally relevant, and practical products to people who want to know and love Christ deeply. Through <em>The Message</em> Bible, books and Bible studies, NavPress brings positive spiritual movement to hearts and lives.</p>\n  <div class=\"read-more\"><a href=\"http://www.navpress.com/\">Read More</a></div>\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"feature fourcol\">\n  <figure><a href=\"http://www.youtube.com/thenavigators\" target=\"_blank\"><span><img title=\"\" alttext=\"\" src=\"www_navigators_org/media/navigators/home/video-gallery.jpg?width=800&amp;amp;height=376&amp;amp;ext=.jpg\"></span></a></figure>\n  <div class=\"title\"><a href=\"http://www.youtube.com/thenavigators\" target=\"_blank\">Our Videos</a></div>\n  <p>Check out our YouTube channel for a large collection of Navigator videos that tell the story of how people around the world live out our calling to make disciples. The series <em>Generations</em> illustrates the biblical concept of creating disciples who will go on to teach others (see 2 Timothy 2:2).</p>\n  <div class=\"read-more\"><a href=\"http://www.youtube.com/thenavigators\">View Now</a></div>\n</div>\n\n  </div>\n  \n  \n\n\n\n<!--So we can affect the background image dynamically-->\n<style>\n  .navigator-history:after {\n  content: url(/www_navigators_org/media/Photos/Home%20Page/bg-Trotman.png?width=705&height=911&ext=.png);\n  }\n</style>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"navigator-history row\">\n  <div class=\"video-player sevencol\">\n    <div class=\"details\">\n      <div class=\"content-item video-player\">\n        <iframe width=\"647\" height=\"363\" src=\"http://www.youtube.com/embed/vYu1FswvKVY\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen=\"\"></iframe>\n      </div>\n    </div>    \n  </div>\n  \n  <div class=\"history-text fivecol last\">\n    <div class=\"title\">Next Door to Everywhere</div>\n    <div class=\"subtitle\">A desire to help others know Him.</div>\n    <div class=\"description\">\n      <p>Since The Navigators' beginnings in 1933, that vision of spreading the love of Christ has flourished. Today, more than 80 years later, we minister with men and women in every line of work, in 100 countries around the worldâwherever there are people who need Christ.
